                <div CLASS="reference"><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">John 3:16</a><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">John 3:3</a><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">Acts 2:38</a></div>
                <div CLASS="scripture">In the resurrection of both the saved and the lost, the one to everlasting life and the other to everlasting seperation from God.</div>
                <div CLASS="reference"><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">1 Thessalonians 4:16, 17</a><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">Revelation 20:11-15</a></div>
                <div CLASS="scripture">In the sacraments of the Lord's Supper to remember and to proclaim the Lord's death and His resurrection'.</div>
                <div CLASS="reference"><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">Corinthians 11:25,26</a></div>
                <div CLASS="scripture">In the church being the body of Christ, and each member being an active part of a local church, fulfilling the Great Commission and in the preparation of the Church as His Bride.</div>
                <div CLASS="reference"><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">Mathew 28:19</a><a HREF="#" TARGET="_blank">Ephesians 4:12; 5:23, 27</a></div>
